<br><br>	<strong>Lifestyle factors:</strong> Health insurance companies may consider an individual's lifestyle factors, such as whether they smoke or drink alcohol, when determining their premiums. Individuals who engage in high-risk behaviors may have higher premiums.
<br><br>	<strong>Geographic location:</strong> The cost of healthcare can vary depending on the region or state, and health insurance premiums may reflect this.
